00:36:24.980 --> 00:36:26.260
We understand we're to pray,

00:36:26.260 --> 00:36:29.140
but he says that we're to pray with thanksgiving.

00:36:29.140 --> 00:36:34.660
There are times that we pray and we can thank God for the answers even before they come.

00:36:35.860 --> 00:36:40.179
Not that we're being presumptuous, but we're trusting that God will work.

00:36:41.059 --> 00:36:44.339
And here, the psalmist in Psalm 118 is having,

00:36:44.899 --> 00:36:48.020
in these next several verses of scripture, this perspective,

00:36:48.020 --> 00:36:52.420
this understanding that God, he's not done working.

00:36:54.020 --> 00:36:55.700
Aren't you thankful for that?

00:36:55.700 --> 00:36:56.820
He's not done working.

00:36:57.540 --> 00:37:02.339
It's not a situation where we can always just look to the past of what God has done.

00:37:02.980 --> 00:37:06.179
It's not just that we look at the present as what God is doing,

00:37:06.179 --> 00:37:11.140
but we can have confidence and we can rejoice that God is still going to.

00:37:11.779 --> 00:37:14.820
Listen, this young man and his wife, they're going to go to Guatemala.

00:37:14.820 --> 00:37:19.860
I'm assuming that they're pretty thankful that God is still going to work

00:37:19.860 --> 00:37:23.619
and that the gospel is still going to be effective when they get there.

00:37:23.619 --> 00:37:24.100
Amen.

00:37:24.980 --> 00:37:27.460
Brother Sommerdorf goes all over preaching.

00:37:27.460 --> 00:37:30.420
Why? Because he's trusting that the promise that God gave,

00:37:30.420 --> 00:37:32.100
that his word would not return void,

00:37:32.100 --> 00:37:35.380
the promise that God gave that through the preaching of the cross,

00:37:36.100 --> 00:37:38.500
the promise that God made to preach the word,

00:37:38.500 --> 00:37:41.300
to be instant in season, out of season, to reprove, rebuke,

00:37:41.300 --> 00:37:43.779
exhort with all longsuffering and doctrine.

00:37:43.779 --> 00:37:46.660
Yes, the time will come when they will not endorse sound doctrine,

00:37:46.660 --> 00:37:48.580
but we still preach the word.

00:37:50.420 --> 00:37:51.700
I preach the word every week.

00:37:51.700 --> 00:37:53.540
Why? Because I believe God will still work.

00:37:54.740 --> 00:37:59.940
I have confidence that not only has God worked,

00:37:59.940 --> 00:38:03.700
not only is God working, but God will continue to work.

00:38:04.740 --> 00:38:06.020
And he says in verse 19,

00:38:06.020 --> 00:38:09.700
open to me the gates of righteousness.

00:38:09.700 --> 00:38:11.700
I will go. Do you see how it's future?

00:38:11.700 --> 00:38:14.820
I will go into them and I will praise the Lord.

00:38:14.820 --> 00:38:18.179
This gate of the Lord into which the righteous shall enter.

00:38:18.179 --> 00:38:23.300
I will praise thee for thou hast heard me and art become my salvation.

00:38:23.300 --> 00:38:28.899
The stone which the builders refused is become the headstone of the corner.

00:38:28.899 --> 00:38:32.899
This is the Lord's doing. It is marvelous in our eyes.

00:38:32.899 --> 00:38:36.020
This is going forward, messianic type prophecy.

00:38:36.020 --> 00:38:39.940
We find in verse 24, this is the day which the Lord hath made.

00:38:39.940 --> 00:38:42.340
We will rejoice and be glad in it.

00:38:42.340 --> 00:38:44.580
Save now, I beseech thee, O Lord.

00:38:44.580 --> 00:38:48.580
O Lord, I beseech thee, send now prosperity.

00:38:48.580 --> 00:38:51.460
Blessed be he that cometh in the name of the Lord.

00:38:51.460 --> 00:38:54.340
We have blessed you out of the house of the Lord.

00:38:54.340 --> 00:38:57.619
God is the Lord which hath showed us light.

00:38:57.619 --> 00:39:02.020
Bind the sacrifice with cords even under the horns of the altar.

00:39:02.020 --> 00:39:06.979
And then as we read by way of introduction, thou art my God.

00:39:07.859 --> 00:39:09.380
And I will praise thee.

00:39:09.380 --> 00:39:12.260
Thou art my God. I will exalt thee.

00:39:12.260 --> 00:39:19.059
Oh, give thanks unto the Lord for he is good, for his mercy endureth forever.

00:39:19.619 --> 00:39:23.859
It is good for us to take time to praise and to exalt our God.

00:39:24.739 --> 00:39:30.419
It is good for us to take and evaluate some things as the psalmist does here

00:39:30.419 --> 00:39:35.700
and just step back from the busyness of all that goes on around us.

00:39:36.179 --> 00:39:39.539
Get our eyes off of all of the things that bother us.

00:39:39.539 --> 00:39:41.220
Listen, there are some things that bother you.

00:39:41.780 --> 00:39:43.299
Come on, I know there are.

00:39:44.419 --> 00:39:46.419
Get your eyes off them circumstances that bother you.

00:39:47.380 --> 00:39:49.619
Get your eyes on God who satisfies.

00:39:52.260 --> 00:39:53.140
He's my God.

00:39:55.220 --> 00:39:59.460
He's always good and his mercy endureth forever.

00:40:00.660 --> 00:40:01.380
This evening,

00:40:01.380 --> 00:40:02.800
How's my praise?

00:40:02.800 --> 00:40:04.760
How's your praise?

00:40:04.760 --> 00:40:07.000
How we doing praising the Lord?

00:40:07.000 --> 00:40:10.960
I asked this question on Wednesday night,

00:40:10.960 --> 00:40:13.000
just this past Wednesday.

00:40:13.000 --> 00:40:14.480
We looked at Psalm 119.

00:40:14.480 --> 00:40:18.280
I will talk you of all his wondrous works.

00:40:18.280 --> 00:40:20.680
And I said that the average person

00:40:20.680 --> 00:40:24.300
speaks 10,000 to 16,000 words every day.

00:40:26.520 --> 00:40:29.680
That number, there's some factors

00:40:29.680 --> 00:40:32.400
that determine the exact number.

00:40:32.400 --> 00:40:35.680
Of course, what you do for a profession

00:40:35.680 --> 00:40:37.840
will have an impact on that number.

00:40:37.840 --> 00:40:40.640
Your gender will have an impact on that number.

00:40:40.640 --> 00:40:43.940
And your personality will have an impact on that number.

00:40:45.160 --> 00:40:50.120
But how many of our words are used praising God?

00:40:50.120 --> 00:40:51.360
How many people have you talked to

00:40:51.360 --> 00:40:54.280
this past four days since Wednesday?

00:40:55.400 --> 00:40:57.600
How many of them heard you praising God?

00:40:57.600 --> 00:40:59.720
With how many of your words?

00:40:59.720 --> 00:41:02.560
Because the psalmist says, thou art my God.

00:41:02.560 --> 00:41:05.000
I will praise thee.

00:41:05.000 --> 00:41:06.760
Thou art my God.

00:41:06.760 --> 00:41:09.320
I will exalt thee.

00:41:09.320 --> 00:41:13.120
And this evening, he is worthy to be praised.

00:41:13.120 --> 00:41:15.680
He is worthy to be exalted.

00:41:15.680 --> 00:41:18.600
And we see so many reasons in Psalm 118.

00:41:18.600 --> 00:41:20.840
And it's not an exhaustive list.

00:41:20.840 --> 00:41:22.920
There's so many other things that you could go to

00:41:22.920 --> 00:41:24.680
and look at this evening.

00:41:24.720 --> 00:41:27.440
But what a power-packed psalm

00:41:28.720 --> 00:41:32.520
of why the psalmist is rejoicing in the way that he is.

00:41:32.520 --> 00:41:35.120
Do you know tonight that the God of the universe

00:41:35.120 --> 00:41:36.600
is your God?

00:41:36.600 --> 00:41:41.560
Can you say, as the psalmist said, thou art my God?

00:41:41.560 --> 00:41:44.560
And if so, are you praising him?

00:41:44.560 --> 00:41:46.040
Are you exalting him?

00:41:46.040 --> 00:41:48.000
Because we ought to be.

00:41:48.000 --> 00:41:48.860
We ought to be.

00:41:48.860 --> 00:41:49.700
Let's pray.

00:41:49.700 --> 00:41:50.840
Father, we love you.

00:41:50.840 --> 00:41:52.320
We thank you so much for loving us.

00:41:52.320 --> 00:41:53.880
Thank you that you're our God.

00:41:54.920 --> 00:41:55.800
Lord, I don't know.

00:41:55.800 --> 00:41:58.760
I've not heard every single person's personal testimony

00:41:58.760 --> 00:42:01.020
of salvation in this room this evening.

00:42:01.020 --> 00:42:03.180
But for most, I have.

00:42:04.480 --> 00:42:07.380
God, I believe that the majority of us tonight,

00:42:07.380 --> 00:42:10.500
if not all of us, could say, thou art my God.

00:42:10.500 --> 00:42:12.680
The question before us is,

00:42:12.680 --> 00:42:15.240
how are we doing in this area of praise?

00:42:15.240 --> 00:42:16.440
We were challenged this morning

00:42:16.440 --> 00:42:19.080
on how we're doing in the area of prayer,

00:42:19.080 --> 00:42:20.540
to be a praying church.

00:42:21.760 --> 00:42:23.059
But not only to be a praying church,

00:42:23.059 --> 00:42:26.380
but to be a praising church.

00:42:26.380 --> 00:42:28.900
Not this nonsense of praise and worship

00:42:28.900 --> 00:42:30.980
and carnality and fleshly.

00:42:30.980 --> 00:42:34.279
No, I'm talking about God honoring,

00:42:34.279 --> 00:42:37.380
godly, biblical praise.

00:42:37.380 --> 00:42:38.980
You are worthy.

00:42:38.980 --> 00:42:41.760
We will praise you for all of eternity.

00:42:41.760 --> 00:42:45.500
I pray that you'd help us now to start every day.

00:42:45.500 --> 00:42:47.740
Would you help us to say, as the psalmist said there

00:42:47.740 --> 00:42:52.740
in Psalm 118 and verse 28, thou art my God.

00:42:52.860 --> 00:42:54.820
I will praise thee.

00:42:54.820 --> 00:42:57.419
Thou art my God.

00:42:57.419 --> 00:43:00.220
I will exalt thee.

00:43:00.220 --> 00:43:02.220
Would you move and work in hearts and lives

00:43:02.220 --> 00:43:04.180
as only you can, and we'll give you the honor

00:43:04.180 --> 00:43:06.820
and the glory, for it's in Christ's name we pray.

